5 § 380. ADMINISTRATIVE PENALTY
6 Consistent with chapter 1 of this title, the Secretary may assess an
7 administrative penalty upon determining that a person has violated a rule
8 issued under this chapter or has violated this chapter in the following manner:
9 (1) distributed a specialty fertilizer, plant amendment, plant
10 biostimulant, soil amendment beneficial substance, or lime without first
11 obtaining the appropriate product registration;
12 (2) distributed a fertilizer, plant amendment, plant biostimulant, soil
13 amendment beneficial substance, or lime without appropriate and accurate
14 labeling, including when a beneficial substance label does not reflect its
15 composition;
16 (3) distributed any adulterated fertilizer, beneficial substance, or lime;
17 (4) failed to disclose on the label sources of potentially deleterious
18 components;
19 (3)(5) failed to report or to accurately report the amount and form of
20 each grade of fertilizer distributed in Vermont on an annual basis;
